expectation is to have a well-documented and organized repository that serves as both a learning resource and a practical guide for setting up and managing a home lab environment using modern DevOps practices.
Here is a suggested directory structure for the "DevOps Home Lab Project":

homelab-project/
├─ docs/
│  ├─ 00_system_setup.md
│  ├─ 01_docker.md
│  ├─ 02_kubernetes_intro.md
│  ├─ 03_cicd.md
│  ├─ 04_networking_ingress_tls.md
│  ├─ 05_observability.md
│  ├─ 06_security_backups.md
│  └─ portfolio.md
├─ projects/basic-stack/
├─ k8s/manifests/
├─ charts/
├─ monitoring/
├─ iac/
├─ .github/workflows/
├─ README.md
└─ CHANGELOG.md
